New Records: Ben Stokes passed 10,000 international runs across all formats.
Key Match Events: England posted a total of 339 for nine.
Netherlands were all out for 179 in 37.2 overs.
Adil Rashid and Moeen Ali took three wickets each.
Teja Nidamanuru top-scored for the Netherlands with 41 runs.
Pre-Game Insights: There were questions about whether England could sink any lower against the Netherlands before the match.
Post-Match Reflections: The result lifted England to seventh place in the World Cup table.
Pressure was building on England’s leadership pairing of Jos Buttler and Matthew Mott.
A top-eight finish for a spot in the 2025 Champions Trophy could require a third victory against Pakistan.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Ben Stokes' century was described as incendiary.
England's fielding had previously been an area of credit despite two drops in this match.
Ben Stokes' performance was a reminder of his elite status as an ODI batter.
Ben Stokes' knee injury is booked for an imminent operation.
